,"attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5772"},"text":"section 5772 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, prior to editorial reclassification and renumbering as this section. Some section numbers or references in amendment notes below reflect the classification of such sections or references prior to editorial reclassification."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"id4cef8423-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/415/s403"},"text":"section 403 of Pub. L. 93–415","children":[],"tail":" amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s3883"},"text":"section 3883 of Title 42","children":[],"tail":", The Public Health and Welfare, and was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/115/s10"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–115, § 10","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1977-10-03"},"text":"Oct. 3, 1977","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/1061"},"text":"91 Stat. 1061","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tII/s12221/a/4"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. C, title II, § 12221(a)(4)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1894"},"text":"116 Stat. 1894","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"id4cef8424-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2024—Par. (5). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/65"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–65","children":[],"tail":" added par. (5)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2018—Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/267/s2/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–267, § 2(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/393/s202/b/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–393, § 202(b)(1)","children":[],"tail":", amended section identically, adding par. (1) and striking out former par. (1) which read as follows: “the term ‘missing child’ means any individual less than 18 years of age whose whereabouts are unknown to such individual’s legal custodian;”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Par. (4). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/267/s2/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–267, § 2(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":"–(4), and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/393/s202/b/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–393, § 202(b)(2)","children":[],"tail":"–(4), amended section identically, adding par. (4)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—Par. (1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/295"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–295","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of par. (1) by striking out “or” at the end of subpar. (A), inserting “or” after the semicolon in subpar. (B), and adding after subpar. (B) subpar. (C) “the individual is an individual under 21 years of age who is displaced from the habitual residence of that individual as a result of an emergency or major disaster (as those terms are defined in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s5122"},"text":"section 5122 of this title","children":[],"tail":").”, could not be executed because of the prior amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–248","children":[],"tail":", see below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/248"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–248","children":[],"tail":", which directed amendment of “Section 403(1) of the Comprehensive Crime Control Act of 1984 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s5772"},"text":"42 U.S.C. 5772","children":[],"tail":")” by substituting a semicolon at end for “if—” through subpar. (B), was executed by substituting a semicolon for “if—”and subpars. (A) and (B) of par. (1) of this section, which is section 403 of the Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention Act of 1974, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/415"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–415","children":[],"tail":", as added by section 660 of the Comprehensive Crime Control Act of 1984, to reflect the probable intent of Congress. Prior to amendment, subpars. (A) and (B) read as follows:"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(A) the circumstances surrounding such individual’s disappearance indicate that such individual may possibly have been removed by another from the control of such individual’s legal custodian without such custodian’s consent; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(B) the circumstances of the case strongly indicate that such individual is likely to be abused or sexually exploited;”.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—Par. (3). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/71"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–71","children":[],"tail":" added par. (3)."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"id4cef8425-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"id4cef8426-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 2018 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/267"},"text":"Pub. L. 115–267","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-10-11"},"text":"Oct. 11, 2018","children":[],"tail":", and applicable to fiscal years beginning after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2018-09-30"},"text":"Sept. 30, 2018","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/115/267/s4"},"text":"section 4 of Pub. L. 115–267","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t34/s11291"},"text":"section 11291 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
